  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "RF",
    "text": "This book, entitled was written by Elinor Brecher. We were asked to tell our story. This is the story of many Schindler survivors. In the book are some pictures of our family. And I will explain to you in a moment who they are. [PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] This is my picture with my family taken in-- during summer vacation in [? Marianbat, ?] Czechoslovakia. On the left is my father, Aron Schonthal. This is I, as a young girl, my mother, Bella Schonthal, and my brother, Paul Schonthal. [PAUSES FOR 22 SECONDS] These are my parents, Bella and Aron Schonthal, taken during our son's bar mitzvah, in 1964. [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] This is my husband, Lew. This is my husband, Lewis and I. It's a picture taken in our Boca Raton home in Florida in 1993. [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] These are our two sons, Arthur and Lester. [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Arthur is on the right. Lester is on the left. [PAUSES FOR 13 SECONDS] This is our delightful family-- our son, Arthur, and his wife, Paulette, with their three children, Alicia, Rebecca, and Gabriella, and our son, Lester, and his wife, Trudy, with their three daughters, Shoshanna, Ariel, and Laila. [PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] These are our delightful six granddaughters. We are extremely proud of them, and we hope that as the grandchildren of Holocaust survivors, they will keep the history of Holocaust alive. We wish them all at the luck in the world.",
